\section{Future Directions and Calls for Collaboration}

This paper represents the first step in a broader research program. We identify several crucial directions requiring expert collaboration:

\subsection{General Relativity and Curved Timespace}

The framework developed here applies to \textbf{locally flat patches} of timespace. Extending to curved Reilly timespace---where mass-energy curves the geometry---requires:
\begin{itemize}
\item Recasting the Einstein field equations in $(+,+,+,+)$ signature
\item Understanding how the Ricci tensor emerges from information-theoretic constraints
\item Connecting the metric structure to information storage requirements (Bekenstein bound)
\item Reformulating geodesic deviation and tidal forces
\end{itemize}

We conjecture that general relativity can be recast as \textbf{information geometry}: the metric tensor encodes how much information can be stored in each region, with curvature arising from information generation rates. This will be explored in a forthcoming paper on gravity and the wholographic principle.

\textbf{Collaboration needed:} Relativists, differential geometers, and information theorists familiar with Riemannian geometry in signature $(+,+,+,+)$.

\subsection{Twistor Theory and Projective Structure}

The null 3-spaces ($d\tau = 0$) where both light cones flatten to horizontal disks suggest deep connections to:
\begin{itemize}
\item Penrose's twistor theory (where null rays form $\mathbb{CP}^3$)
\item Projective geometry and exotic smooth structures of $\mathbb{R}^4$
\item Spinor structures and the $\text{Spin}(4) = \text{SU}(2) \times \text{SU}(2)$ double cover
\item Understanding why past and future light rays are antipodally identified
\end{itemize}

\textbf{Collaboration needed:} Twistor theorists, geometric topologists, and mathematical physicists familiar with projective spaces and spinor geometry.

\subsection{Quantum Field Theory and Quantum Gravity}

The SO(4) symmetry and Euclidean signature should simplify:
\begin{itemize}
\item Spin-statistics theorem (more natural with compact symmetry group)
\item CPT theorem (connection to antipodal identification)
\item Path integral formulations (Euclidean signature is standard for Wick rotation)
\item Canonical quantization with positive-definite inner product
\end{itemize}

\textbf{Collaboration needed:} QFT theorists, quantum gravity researchers (especially loop quantum gravity and spin foam approaches which already use SO(4)).

\subsection{This is Just the Beginning}

Wheeler's ``It from Bit'' vision can now be realized as ``That From Nat''---with explicit mechanisms connecting information generation to physical reality. We invite the physics community to explore, extend, and test this framework.

